    "title": "Bitcoin core error after disabling block chain pruning and then restarting the application,  error:opening block database",
    "body": "<!-- This issue tracker is only for technical issues related to Bitcoin Core.\r\n\r\nGeneral bitcoin questions and/or support requests are best directed to the Bitcoin StackExchange at https://bitcoin.stackexchange.com.\r\n\r\nFor reporting security issues, please read instructions at https://bitcoincore.org/en/contact/.\r\n\r\nIf the node is \"stuck\" during sync or giving \"block checksum mismatch\" errors, please ensure your hardware is stable by running memtest and observe CPU temperature with a load-test tool such as linpack before creating an issue!\r\n\r\nAny report, issue or feature request related to the GUI should be reported at\r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin-core/gui/issues/\r\n-->\r\n\r\n<!-- Describe the issue -->\r\n\r\nI have attempted to turn of block chain pruning in the options menu, which has required the application to restart.\r\nWhen I have restarted the application I'm faced with this error message and then the program closes.\r\n\r\nThis now happens every time I open the application and wont load to the wallet, It also persists even after I uninstall the entire bitcoin core and re install the bit coin core program and when I go to initial launch the program this again pops up. \r\n\r\nWas working previous but with a pruned block  chain and had no problems, but as soon as I went to options and disabled block chain pruning this was the resulting error I received.\r\n\r\n\"you need to rebuild the data base using -reindex to go back to unpruned mode. This will redownload the entire blockchain. \r\ndo you want to rebuild the block database now?\r\n\r\nok\r\n\r\nerror:opening block database\r\n\r\nok \r\n\r\nprogram closes\"\r\n\r\nIf someone knows what I can do to fix this, many thanks\r\n\r\n<!--- What behavior did you expect? -->\r\n\r\n<!--- What was the actual behavior (provide screenshots if the issue is GUI-related)? -->\r\n\r\n<!--- How reliably can you reproduce the issue, what are the steps to do so? -->\r\n\r\n<!-- What version of Bitcoin Core are you using, where did you get it (website, self-compiled, etc)? -->\r\n\r\n<!-- What type of machine are you observing the error on (OS/CPU and disk type)? -->\r\n\r\n<!-- GUI-related issue? What is your operating system and its version? If Linux, what is your desktop enviro\r\n![Core error2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/95224812/146670460-710c0765-940f-4455-b37d-2727b7eff253.png)\r\n\r\n![Core error1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/95224812/146670458-ecfd58a6-f21e-42c6-be17-f77827e8f9aa.png)\r\nnment and graphical shell? -->\r\n\r\n<!-- Any extra information that might be useful in the debugging process. -->\r\n<!--- This is normally the contents of a `debug.log` or `config.log` file. Raw text or a link to a pastebin type site are preferred. -->\r\n",
